text: Marise Ann Payne (born 29 July 1964) is an Australian politician. She was the Minister for Foreign Affairs in the Morrison Government from 2018 until 2022. She was also named Minister for Women in 2019. She is a member of the Liberal Party. She has been a Senator for New South Wales since 1997. Payne was born in Sydney. She is in a relationship with New South Wales politician Stuart Ayres. ==References== ==Other websites== * Category:1964 births Category:Living people Category:Australian ministers for Foreign Affairs Category:Liberal Party of Australia politicians Category:Members of the Australian Senate Category:Politicians from Sydney
